 Ngqamakhwe - Ngqamakhwe police have appealed to the public to assist with information that can help them solve a murder case. "It is alleged that a man believed to be in his 20s was found with upper body wounds on Sunday morning at Mbeveni Village, Ngqamakhwe," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The deceased has not been identified. No one has been arrested regarding his murder." Capt Manatha said that the deceased is light in complexion. "He was wearing a black jersey and blue jeans. "Anyone who can identify is kindly requested to contact Ngqamakhwe Police at 047 487 0017." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 